WEBVTT

00:00.162 --> 00:04.226
Well, last week, we talked about speak up and share our faith.

00:04.246 --> 00:07.750
And I talked about that I was tired about being on eco mode.

00:07.770 --> 00:08.290
I remember that.

00:08.310 --> 00:10.032
I said, I'm tired of being on eco mode.

00:10.373 --> 00:12.335
I want to go back to sport mode.

00:12.915 --> 00:18.521
And I want you to know that our church is living back in sport mode.

00:18.541 --> 00:23.987
And nothing says sport mode around River Valley Church, like starting a new campus.

00:24.027 --> 00:25.028
How many of you know what I'm talking about?

00:25.428 --> 00:27.090
Nothing says sport mode.

00:27.170 --> 00:32.578
Like we're back on the offensive and we're ready to start a new campus.

00:32.918 --> 00:45.336
And I want to let you know, I talked about it in the vision message in January and I'm ready to reveal it today that we are starting a new campus in 2022 in Maple Grove area.

00:45.396 --> 00:48.780
That is where our next campus is going to be.

00:48.800 --> 00:55.570
And I want to let you know that from our Apple Valley campus,

00:55.810 --> 01:04.704
Caleb and Autumn Graham are the new campus pastors, and I want you to show your appreciation as they answer the call.

01:06.627 --> 01:09.571
They came here from North Dakota, and they've been on staff for a couple years.

01:09.611 --> 01:11.875
They just felt this is the next move for them.

01:11.895 --> 01:15.020
And they gladly accepted that, and we're ready to send them there.

01:15.200 --> 01:17.483
They're going to be assembling a team and a launch team.

01:17.744 --> 01:20.768
And if you're interested in being back on sport mode, all right?

01:21.229 --> 01:24.434
You can text the word Maple Grove to 94,000.

01:24.642 --> 01:27.026
That's the word maple grove to 94,000.

01:27.046 --> 01:30.431
And we will help you to get the info you need.

01:30.471 --> 01:34.057
If you know friends in that area, they're like, is there a river valley church come that way?

01:34.097 --> 01:35.639
Matter of fact, I got an email this week.

01:35.679 --> 01:36.961
So he said, I have a friend in New York.

01:37.262 --> 01:38.444
Is there a river valley in New York?

01:38.464 --> 01:39.165
I'm like, not yet.

01:39.185 --> 01:40.126
We're going to maple grove.

01:40.547 --> 01:41.328
All right, yeah.

01:41.348 --> 01:42.911
I get requests all the time.

01:42.951 --> 01:43.532
Where's the next one?

01:43.552 --> 01:44.413
Where's the next one?

01:44.433 --> 01:45.956
But the next one is maple grove.

01:45.976 --> 01:50.002
So if you're interested again, or if you have friends in that area and they want to get the info,

01:50.082 --> 01:54.548
And even if you're just leaning in, you feel like it's part of what your next step is to do.

01:55.349 --> 02:00.076
Please text the words Maple Grove 94,000 and congratulations to Caleb and Autumn.

02:00.116 --> 02:02.159
We think you're gonna do an amazing job.

02:02.620 --> 02:03.621
You're ready for this.

02:03.641 --> 02:04.282
You're ready for this.

02:04.602 --> 02:06.044
We're back on sport mode.

02:08.628 --> 02:17.541
Now today, after we did speak up and share your faith, I wanna talk to you about being hot and being salty for God.

02:17.621 --> 02:18.482
Hot and salty.

02:19.362 --> 02:19.822
All right.

02:19.843 --> 02:21.604
Some of you are like, where's the scripture for that?

02:21.644 --> 02:22.245
I'll get there.

02:22.385 --> 02:23.687
All right.

02:23.707 --> 02:24.167
I believe this.

02:24.247 --> 02:28.351
I believe the time for casual Christianity in America is over.

02:29.212 --> 02:30.534
I believe it's time for the church.

02:30.594 --> 02:33.957
It's got to stop being compartmentalized weekends only.

02:34.238 --> 02:37.301
If it doesn't inconvenience you, it's not too much to ask.

02:37.321 --> 02:39.763
If it's half hearted, half baked, half lit, whatever.

02:39.783 --> 02:46.130
You know, there's no more that it's time to go all in and say it's time for the church to be hot

02:46.242 --> 02:48.446
and salty, and you're still wondering where that verse is.

02:48.506 --> 02:49.548
All right, turn to me.

02:49.568 --> 03:00.228
Matthew chapter five, verse 13, Jesus is speaking and he says, you are the salt of the earth, but if the salt loses its saltiness, how can it be made salty again?

03:00.509 --> 03:05.618
It's no longer good for anything except to be thrown out and trampled underfoot.

03:06.146 --> 03:08.049
You are the light of the world.

03:08.350 --> 03:10.554
A town built on a hill cannot be hidden.

03:10.894 --> 03:13.378
Neither do people light a lamp and put it under a bowl.

03:13.639 --> 03:17.465
Instead, they put it on its stand and it gives light to everyone in the house.

03:17.786 --> 03:25.219
In the same way, let your light shine before others that they may see your good deeds and glorify your Father in heaven.

03:26.000 --> 03:29.366
That's where I get it that you are supposed to be hot and salty.

03:29.386 --> 03:31.890
And you say, wait a minute, it says light.

03:31.970 --> 03:34.694
Don't you think you should say we should be bright and salty?

03:34.995 --> 03:42.146
I just want to tell you right now, when Jesus was talking to them, they were not thinking about flashlights, on, off, on.

03:42.366 --> 03:43.488
They were thinking about that.

03:43.768 --> 03:46.072
They were thinking about fire.

03:46.132 --> 03:54.725
They were thinking about candles and lamps and bonfires and bigger fires.

03:55.246 --> 04:00.754
Any light that was being done at that point was light that was coming from fire.

04:00.962 --> 04:05.506
So give me the latitude because I think the church doesn't need to just be on.

04:05.807 --> 04:07.949
The church needs to be on fire.

04:07.969 --> 04:12.473
The church needs to be hot right now and saying, we're gonna be part of this.

04:12.733 --> 04:15.616
We're gonna be hot and we're going to be salty.

04:16.436 --> 04:22.142
Now, I'll start with that with being hot, with being the light, with being the flame of God for this world.

04:22.963 --> 04:30.930
It's the only explicit statement that Jesus states to his followers that it's something that he is also.

04:31.458 --> 04:31.959
Follow me.

04:32.419 --> 04:33.720
It's the only explicit statement.

04:33.741 --> 04:37.004
She's like, you are the light of the world.

04:37.024 --> 04:39.427
You're gonna go out and be a hot flame to this world.

04:39.687 --> 04:42.110
You are the light of the world.

04:42.911 --> 04:45.533
Now it's interesting, he calls himself the light of the world.

04:46.074 --> 04:51.100
He calls you and I the light of the world and he calls himself the light of the world.

04:51.140 --> 04:59.509
Matter of fact, he called his disciples the light of the world before he called himself the light of the world.

05:00.189 --> 05:00.690
Think of that.

05:01.346 --> 05:12.123
And he's saying, if you are my disciples, if you said yes to Jesus, if you have given your life, if you're a Christ follower, you don't have a choice, you are the light of the world.

05:13.125 --> 05:22.640
Jesus said, I want you to go out into the world and be that light in a world that's so dark, in a world that's so desperate, in a world that's gone mad with evil.

05:22.660 --> 05:26.386
He's like, I want you to go out and be the light, the church,

05:26.498 --> 05:30.224
has to be hot with a flame being the light to this world.

05:30.524 --> 05:33.188
And we've been given the honor and privilege to do that.

05:34.030 --> 05:34.791
It's an amazing thing.

05:35.792 --> 05:41.201
You didn't say, all right, you guys just follow me and study and stay huddled up in church.

05:41.902 --> 05:43.945
And I'll let the angels go be the light.

05:44.005 --> 05:44.726
I didn't do that.

05:45.447 --> 05:54.802
He said, you guys, you, the church, all of you are all the light, you get to go out in the world and be this flame for me

05:54.914 --> 05:57.218
this bright thing for my glory.

05:57.598 --> 05:58.780
And he's like, you're going out there.

05:59.481 --> 06:00.983
And he says, I don't want you to be hidden.

06:01.404 --> 06:04.228
I want you to be on a stand.

06:04.268 --> 06:05.330
I want you to be shown.

06:05.771 --> 06:13.923
Again, we think like, the reason I wanted to go to hot and not just, you know, the light or bright was, as I was studying for this, I really did.

06:13.963 --> 06:15.586
I was thinking like, it's a flashlight.

06:15.606 --> 06:17.369
Like I'm the, you know, we're the light.

06:17.389 --> 06:17.489
Okay.

06:17.789 --> 06:18.430
Yeah.

06:18.450 --> 06:19.251
And then I was like, wait a minute.

06:19.271 --> 06:21.815
It's so easy on, off, off, off, off.

06:21.835 --> 06:23.538
And I was like, no, they were like,

06:23.842 --> 06:30.049
If you're following Jesus, you're a flame, and you're on fire, and you are hot for God, and they were protecting it.

06:30.249 --> 06:31.590
They didn't want it to blow out.

06:31.811 --> 06:34.934
They couldn't just be on off, they could do that.

06:35.214 --> 06:44.224
They were like, if we're on, there's a flame, there's a passion, there's a burning, and the only thing they could do is hide it, and Jesus is like, I don't want you to hide it.

06:44.244 --> 06:49.490
And so I'm like, okay, it's got to be that God wants us to be on fire for him,

06:49.602 --> 06:53.786
passionately filled up with the power of the Holy Spirit, and we're not gonna hide.

06:53.806 --> 06:57.470
We're gonna go out there and be bold and say, here's what we believe.

06:58.371 --> 06:59.812
Here's what God's called us to do.

07:00.533 --> 07:09.661
Now, when you're the light and when you're hot for God, that's attractive to some and it's attacked by others.

07:11.143 --> 07:18.450
When you're gonna be a light, when you're gonna be a flame, when you're gonna bring the light of God into this world that the Bible says loves darkness,

07:18.594 --> 07:23.964
It's going to be celebrated by some and it's going to be attacked by others.

07:24.585 --> 07:29.875
And so let me just give you a few things that are celebrated about being hot, about being the flame for God, about being the light.

07:30.096 --> 07:32.260
And if I use light, flashlight, hot, do you get it?

07:32.580 --> 07:33.642
You understand what I'm saying?

07:35.306 --> 07:39.794
Now, one of the things that light does when it comes into a room is it illuminates.

07:39.938 --> 07:43.223
and it brightens up everything, and it shows what's in the room.

07:43.503 --> 07:44.985
It shows what's available.

07:45.286 --> 07:49.031
It just, it kind of brought, it lets everybody see what's there.

07:49.071 --> 07:53.998
And I'll say this, the older I get, the more light I need.

07:54.038 --> 07:55.059
How many know what I'm talking about?

07:55.620 --> 08:03.651
Yeah, I mean, the older I get, the more I go to those restaurants and I go to a restaurant that's nice, it has ambiance, a little dark, and I look at that menu and I'm like, I can't see a thing.

08:05.013 --> 08:06.195
I'm like, hold it that far away.

08:06.275 --> 08:08.338
I back a hold it across the table, still can't see it.

08:08.738 --> 08:13.044
I get the flashlight out shining, and you're like, how many have turned on your phone?

08:13.345 --> 08:17.431
Honestly, you've turned it on, turned that light on, and you blind everyone in the restaurant, right?

08:18.632 --> 08:26.824
And so I found this app, and I can just turn my light on real suddenly, just at like 10%, and then it magnifies, somebody's shining their light, turn that light off in the turn.

08:28.567 --> 08:29.408
It's like a concert.

08:29.648 --> 08:30.710
We're all like, oh.

08:31.791 --> 08:32.332
But I do that.

08:32.653 --> 08:33.334
I've got to see it.

08:33.374 --> 08:33.955
I've got to see.

08:34.235 --> 08:35.156
And so I'm looking at that.

08:35.497 --> 08:36.338
How many have heard of that?

08:36.418 --> 08:37.439
Blackout dining.

08:37.459 --> 08:38.080
Have you heard of that?

08:38.120 --> 08:38.900
Blackout dining?

08:39.941 --> 08:44.986
Blackout dining is where people go into a room and you sit down and then they turn out all the lights.

08:46.228 --> 08:50.091
The wait staff has like infrared things so they can put the food in front of you.

08:50.332 --> 08:51.192
You can't see a thing.

08:51.493 --> 08:52.093
It's pitch black.

08:52.133 --> 08:53.074
Blackout dining.

08:53.094 --> 08:55.937
And you're there and they put stuff in front of you and they say go ahead and eat.

08:56.518 --> 08:56.958
Not me.

08:59.601 --> 08:59.921
Not me.

08:59.981 --> 09:00.662
I want to see it.

09:00.682 --> 09:03.604
How many know like I'm assessing what to start with?

09:03.664 --> 09:05.266
Like all right, that right there.

09:05.378 --> 09:07.883
All right, we're starting right there.

09:07.903 --> 09:09.726
I'm eating with my eyes first.

09:10.788 --> 09:12.271
I'm eating with my eyes first.

09:12.291 --> 09:13.092
So here's the beautiful thing.

09:14.515 --> 09:16.599
The world is eating with their eyes first.

09:18.022 --> 09:22.610
And when we come into their world, we illuminate who Jesus is.

09:23.394 --> 09:25.478
And they get to read the menu, the light is on.

09:25.698 --> 09:26.420
And they're like, wait, wait, wait.

09:26.440 --> 09:28.103
I didn't know that that was a spiritual option.

09:28.443 --> 09:30.287
I didn't know that that hope could be available.

09:30.567 --> 09:32.871
I didn't know that that peace could come into my life.

09:32.891 --> 09:34.635
I didn't know they're looking at the menu.

09:34.875 --> 09:35.576
You are light.

09:35.596 --> 09:37.480
You are bringing that into their world.

09:37.820 --> 09:39.523
And you're illuminating something.

09:39.804 --> 09:40.846
And it's beautiful.

09:40.906 --> 09:45.174
They're eating with their eyes first before they can ever taste and see that God is good.

09:45.194 --> 09:47.538
They're looking at you, the menu.

09:48.930 --> 09:50.051
It's a responsibility.

09:50.351 --> 09:52.233
You are the light of the world.

09:52.273 --> 09:58.179
We share this with Jesus and we're pointing people to Jesus, but we are what they're seeing first.

09:59.380 --> 10:04.525
I mean, when I go into a place and I eat with my eyes first, sometimes I'll look and be like, sorry guys, it's too dirty.

10:05.505 --> 10:06.747
Too dirty, we can't eat there.

10:07.027 --> 10:08.729
I don't know about you, sometimes I go into a bathroom.

10:08.749 --> 10:10.931
I'll look at the bathroom, oh, sorry, I'm out, I'm out.

10:11.251 --> 10:18.898
I'll never forget we were on a global team and we were in China and we were there on the global team and it was the only place that we could eat

10:19.010 --> 10:35.706
in the town and Logan went early and went into the bathroom and he came out before the food got there and he said, hey dad, dad, when you pray over the meal of the day he goes, really pray, really pray, like really, don't do like a thanks for the food God, you know, like really pray, it's dirty.

10:37.227 --> 10:39.269
Hey, the world is reading the menu.

10:40.450 --> 10:41.031
Are you bright?

10:41.131 --> 10:42.712
Are you pointing people to Jesus?

10:43.333 --> 10:48.978
Are you saying, I understand what you've called me to do and I want to be on fire for you.

10:49.474 --> 10:55.122
Another thing that the light can do and that the flame can do,

10:55.394 --> 10:56.455
It can warn people.

10:56.795 --> 10:58.637
There's a lot of depression in this world.

10:58.878 --> 11:00.740
There's a lot of misery in this world.

11:01.000 --> 11:08.548
There's a lot of people that have just a heaviness on them, and the light can come in there, and it can warm them, and it can inspire them.

11:08.768 --> 11:09.909
How many know what I'm talking about?

11:09.929 --> 11:21.682
The light can inspire, and I think about this, like, Minnesotans, people that are watching online, if you're not from Minnesota and you're watching online, we love that you're part of our church, but you gotta understand where, like, what we are in Minnesota, like,

11:21.730 --> 11:25.997
It can be gloomy and 70 degrees, and Minnesotans are depressed.

11:26.758 --> 11:28.101
We're like, it's overcast.

11:28.161 --> 11:29.002
It's kind of gloomy.

11:29.443 --> 11:30.425
I can't see the sun.

11:30.485 --> 11:31.106
It's kind of gloomy.

11:31.366 --> 11:33.289
It can be minus 20 and studying.

11:33.310 --> 11:35.133
We're like, dah, dah, dah, dah, dah, dah, dah.

11:35.734 --> 11:36.495
Coming into church.

11:36.695 --> 11:37.617
We're like, it's fine.

11:37.677 --> 11:38.679
It's minus 20.

11:38.959 --> 11:40.802
Garden start, but the sun is shining.

11:41.083 --> 11:42.064
The light is there.

11:42.164 --> 11:42.886
I feel good.

11:43.286 --> 11:44.609
We could not live in Seattle.

11:44.629 --> 11:45.490
None of us, all right.

11:47.042 --> 11:54.309
But we can inspire, and I believe there's lots of Christians are partly cloudy with approaching rain and fog coming after that.

11:54.810 --> 12:02.237
We should be the light of the world bringing light and lift into those places and saying, hey, we want to bring this joy into this room.

12:02.257 --> 12:03.138
We want to lift this.

12:03.158 --> 12:08.523
We're bringing the light of God into this atmosphere, and we should be able to lift the room.

12:08.543 --> 12:15.090
And by the way, side note, if anybody ever comes to you with something that is partly cloudy, foggy, maybe even disastrous,

12:15.234 --> 12:19.658
Don't you dare add to the gloom and doom, you bring lift.

12:19.718 --> 12:25.184
If somebody says, hey, just got a diagnosis from the doctor, man, you bring light into that situation.

12:25.464 --> 12:26.986
You bring faith into that.

12:27.006 --> 12:29.088
You be the light like you're supposed to be.

12:29.708 --> 12:31.971
Could you imagine somebody bringing a problem to Jesus?

12:32.011 --> 12:34.473
Like, Jesus, my son has this disease.

12:34.754 --> 12:36.175
Jesus, yeah, bummer.

12:36.195 --> 12:39.578
I had a couple of people die of that in Galilee too, you know?

12:39.799 --> 12:40.679
He went to done that?

12:40.699 --> 12:43.282
He'd say, where's your faith?

12:43.874 --> 12:45.556
He would bring the lift.

12:45.577 --> 12:48.982
If we are supposed to be the light, so we're gonna inspire.

12:49.923 --> 12:54.670
One person said, some people are a joy, wherever they go, others are a joy, whenever they go.

12:54.890 --> 12:59.116
All right, we wanna be a joy, wherever we go.

13:01.260 --> 13:02.662
Because of that, don't dim your light.

13:04.124 --> 13:04.865
Don't dim your light.

13:06.247 --> 13:06.748
Be hot.

13:07.449 --> 13:07.869
Be hot.

13:07.909 --> 13:09.051
Be on fire for God.

13:09.732 --> 13:12.556
Don't be quiet when you should speak up.

13:12.576 --> 13:13.778
That's just dimming the light.

13:14.434 --> 13:15.916
Don't go along with the crowd.

13:15.956 --> 13:17.739
When God says, don't go along with the crowd.

13:18.000 --> 13:19.061
You're dimming the light.

13:20.243 --> 13:21.345
Don't deny the light.

13:21.365 --> 13:22.186
Some people deny the light.

13:22.206 --> 13:22.867
Are you a Christian?

13:22.887 --> 13:23.809
No, no, not me.

13:23.829 --> 13:25.171
My mom, dad are, but not me.

13:25.211 --> 13:26.373
Like I'm totally not.

13:26.393 --> 13:28.997
I'm going to go to church occasionally, but I'm in a small group.

13:29.017 --> 13:29.898
And I'm not a follower.

13:29.958 --> 13:30.840
No way, not me.

13:31.080 --> 13:32.282
And I serve, but not me.

13:32.322 --> 13:33.123
No way.

13:33.444 --> 13:34.365
Don't deny.

13:34.385 --> 13:37.150
And don't let sin dim your light.

13:38.953 --> 13:42.418
Listen to what Ephesians 5.8 says, for you were once in darkness.

13:42.658 --> 13:44.962
but now you are light in the Lord.

13:45.322 --> 13:48.006
Live as children of the light.

13:48.827 --> 13:56.159
That means our everyday behavior should validate that God said over us, you are the light of the world.

13:56.179 --> 13:58.382
When you go out in the world, you're gonna live like the light.

13:58.642 --> 14:06.935
When you're living in your daily life, your behavior is going to say, I understand that I am supposed to be the light to this world.

14:07.716 --> 14:11.602
The place that God has placed me, I'm going to be the light.

14:11.714 --> 14:17.863
And I pray against a flashlight mentality that says on, off, on, off, on, off, on, off for faith.

14:18.223 --> 14:22.709
I pray that we say we are on all the time, all the time.

14:22.990 --> 14:29.879
We are gonna be bright for God and we're not gonna say, you know, I'm gonna let the world dim my light for Jesus.

14:31.021 --> 14:31.822
Let me tell you right now.

14:33.765 --> 14:35.647
I battle some of the thoughts that you have as well.

14:35.707 --> 14:37.650
I watch our world and I see our society.

14:37.858 --> 14:48.113
I was preaching at Shiloh Temple on Saturday morning this weekend, and I walked in the door, and the pastor's wife said, praise God, we didn't have a shooting last night in Minneapolis by our church.

14:48.694 --> 14:49.576
And it just hit me.

14:50.196 --> 14:53.581
And they've had funeral after funeral after funeral, and shooting after shooting after shooting.

14:53.822 --> 14:56.426
And they rejoicing that they had one night without a shooting.

14:57.728 --> 14:58.228
One night.

14:59.310 --> 15:04.658
And I thought this world has gone mad, it's gone dark, it loves violence, it loves crime, it loves hate.

15:04.802 --> 15:06.764
It loves all these things that are wrong.

15:06.804 --> 15:09.207
It's loving the darkness more than the light.

15:09.247 --> 15:12.872
And after a little while, you kind of feel like it's overwhelming darkness.

15:13.192 --> 15:15.816
And God just spoke to me and said, shine brighter.

15:15.896 --> 15:19.240
Like a candle is worthless in the middle of the day.

15:19.300 --> 15:20.141
It's not needed.

15:20.381 --> 15:21.783
But in the night, it's needed.

15:21.843 --> 15:24.446
A flashlight is really not that valuable in the day.

15:24.807 --> 15:27.570
But at night, thank God for a flashlight.

15:28.258 --> 15:32.745
And so right now, I'm saying like praise God that we're right here where we are.

15:33.066 --> 15:35.209
We get to be the bright light.

15:35.229 --> 15:42.421
We get to be hot for God in Minneapolis, St. Paul, in Minnesota, and around this world.

